{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> φοβερός</b>, ά, όν, <br /> (φόβος) <b>fearful,</b> whether <i>active</i> or <i>passive</i>: <br /><Level2><b>__I</b></Level2> <i>active</i>, <b>causing fear, terrible,</b> χρηστήρια φ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 7.139, compare 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Prometheus Vinctus” 127 (_anapaest meter_), “Th.” 78 (Lyric poetry)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>], etc.; ὅμιλος πλήθει -ώτατος <b>formidable</b> only from numbers, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 2.98 (but τὰ τῷ πλήθει φ.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] things which are <b>fearful to</b> the multitude, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Isocrates Orator 1.7, compare 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Phaedo” 67e): with \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<i>infinitive</i>, φ. ἰδεῖν, φ. προσιδέσθαι, <b>fearful</b> to behold, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Persae” 27 (_anapaest meter_), 48 (_anapaest meter_); φ. εἰσιδεῖν 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Phoenissae” 127 (Lyric poetry); φ. προσπολεμῆσαι 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 2.22; φ. Πολυδεύκεα πὺξ ἐρεθίζειν 3rd c.BC: Theocritus Poeta Bucolicus 22.2. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__I.2</b></Level3> <b>regarded with fear,</b> especially with respect to consequences, οὔτε ὅρκος φ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 3.83 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἵππος φ. μὴ ἀνήκεστόν τι ποιήσῃ a horse <b>that makes one fear</b> he will do some mischief, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Hiero” 6.15; σεμνότερος εἶναι καὶ φοβερώτερος δοκεῖ 5th-6th c.BC: Andocides Orator 4.18; φοβεροὶ ἦσαν μὴ ποιήσειαν 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Anabasis” 5.7.2; τοῖς πολεμίοις φοβερώτεροι [prev. author] “Eq.Mag.” 4.11, compare “Ages.” 11.10 (_superlative_): τριήρης φοβερὸν πολεμίοις [prev. author] “Oec.” 8.8; τὸ πρὸ τῶν λυπηρῶν [προσδόκημα] φ. 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Philebus” 32c; φοβερώτατον ἐρημία 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Anabasis” 2.5.9; τὸ φ. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<b>terror, danger,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Lac.” 9.1 \">Refs</a>]; τῶν φοβερῶν ὄντων τῇ πόλει γενέσθαι the things which were <b>dreaded</b> as like ly to happen.., [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “HG” 1.4.17 \">Refs</a>]; φοβερόν [ἐστι] μὴ.. there is <b>reason to dread</b> that.., [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Hier.” 1.12, compare “Cyr.” 7.5.22 \">Refs</a>]; ἀγγέλλεσθαι ἐπὶ τὸ φοβερώτατον to be <b>fearfully exaggerated,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.BC: Dionysius Halicarnassensis 1.57. \">Refs 1st c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__I.3</b></Level3> Rhet., of style, <b>impressive, awe-inspiring,</b> τὸ κάλλος τὸ Θουκυδίδου φ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Pomp.” 3; τὸ φ. [prev. author] “Lys.” 13; Ὅμηρος παίζων -ώτερος 4th c.BC: Demetrius Phalereus Rhetor “Demetrius on Style” 130. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <i>passive</i>, <b>afraid, timid,</b> ἐκτέταμαι φοβερὰν φρένα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Tyrannus” 153 (Lyric poetry), compare 7th-6th c.BC: Alcaeus Lyricus 97, 5th c.BC: Pherecrates Comicus 245; ὄμμα 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Iphigenia Aulidensis” 620: opposed to θαρσαλέος, 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 2.3, 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Institutio Cyri (Cyropaedia)” 3.3 19 (_comparative_)\">Refs 7th c.BC+</a>]; φ. τὴν ψυχήν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Oec.” 7.25 \">Refs</a>]; σκοπεῖν εἰ φοβεροί (i.e. οἱ πῶλοι) [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Respublica” 413d; φ. ποιεῖν τινα [prev. author] “Lg.” 647c; φ. εἰς τὸ τολμᾶν [prev. work] 649d. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.2</b></Level3> <b>caused by fear, troubled, panic,</b> ἀναχώρησις [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 4.128; φοβερὰ ὄσσοις ὁμίχλα προσῇξε 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Prometheus Vinctus” 144 (Lyric poetry)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; φ. φροντίδες <b>anxious</b> thoughts, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Theages” 127b. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__III</b></Level2> <i>adverb</i> <b>-ρῶς</b> <b>threateningly, in a terrifying manner,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Lysias Orator 24.15, cf. LXX.3Mac.5.45, etc.\">LXX+5th c.BC+</a>]: <i>comparative</i>, -ώτερον φθέγγεσθαι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Symposium” 1.10 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: <i>superlative</i>, -ώτατα ἰδεῖν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Cyr.” 8.3.5. \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__III.2</b></Level3> <b>timidly,</b> -ώτατα ἔχειν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Eq.Mag.” 8.20. \">Refs</a>]","strongNumber":"G5398","accentedUnicode":"φοβερός","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G0870","matchingForm":"ἀφόβως","stepTransliteration":"afobōs","gloss":"fearlessly","_zh_tw_Gloss":"無懼怕","_es_Gloss":"sin temor","_zh_Gloss":"无惧怕"},{"strongNumber":"G1629","matchingForm":"ἐκφοβέω","stepTransliteration":"ekfobeō","gloss":"to terrify","_zh_tw_Gloss":"威嚇","_es_Gloss":"aterrorizar  ","_zh_Gloss":"威吓"},{"strongNumber":"G1719","matchingForm":"ἔμφοβος","stepTransliteration":"emfobos","gloss":"afraid","_zh_tw_Gloss":"驚怕, 恐懼","_es_Gloss":"asustado","_zh_Gloss":"惊怕, 恐惧"},{"strongNumber":"G4422","matchingForm":"πτοέω","stepTransliteration":"ptoeō","gloss":"to frighten","_zh_tw_Gloss":"驚惶","_es_Gloss":"espantar","_zh_Gloss":"惊惶"},{"strongNumber":"G4423","matchingForm":"πτόησις","stepTransliteration":"ptoēsis","gloss":"fear","_zh_tw_Gloss":"恐嚇","_es_Gloss":"miedo","_zh_Gloss":"恐吓"},{"strongNumber":"G4426","matchingForm":"πτύρομαι","stepTransliteration":"pturomai","gloss":"to frighten","_zh_tw_Gloss":"驚